		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Sumter So. Ca.</placeName> <date>May 13th&#47;58</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Knowing your ability to<lb/> diffuse lights on a subject that I am<lb/> comparatively ignorant of&#44; and believing<lb/> in your perfect willingness to aid the<lb/> benighted.  I propose asking you a<lb/> few questions on the subject of our<lb/> religion.  I unfortunately have been <lb/>very imperfectly instructed myself<lb/> &#38; living as I do out of a congregation<lb/> have no means of instructing my<lb/> children&#59; I have a son a youth of<lb/> 17&#44; whose mind is very mature<lb/> circumstances have induced him<lb/> to open a correspondence with me<lb/> on the subject of religion &#38; he pro<lb/> pounds the following questions to me.</p>
				<p>1 Why are you a Jew&#63;</p>
				<p>2 What are the fundamental grounds<lb/> of the Jewish belief&#63;  3 What are<lb/> your ideas of a saviour&#63;  4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> What<lb/> is your belief in regard to salvation<lb/> &#38; damnation&#63;  5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Do you believe in<lb/> the divinity of the Bible&#44; or do you<lb/> think it an allegory&#63;  These he says</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>are a few questions he would like me<lb/> to answer&#44; as he is ignorant of his<lb/> creed he desires <hi rend="underline">reasons</hi> for his<lb/> faith &#38; objects to taking his belief<lb/> from another.  My son is at present<lb/> in <placeName>Washington City</placeName> but proposes<lb/> visiting my sister <persName>Mrs. G. C. Levy</persName> next<lb/> month.  I propose answering his<lb/> queries as soon as I get <hi rend="underline">your</hi> answers<lb/> &#38; would be very much obliged<lb/> if you would direct my atten<lb/>tion to such books as contain<lb/> the <hi rend="underline">strongest</hi> arguments in support<lb/> of our faith that I may not only<lb/> be able to instruct him but <hi rend="underline">my</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">self</hi> &#38; <hi rend="underline">five</hi> other <hi rend="underline">sons</hi> at home.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">When my son reaches your<lb/> city I shall endeavour to bring<lb/> you together &#38; I feel assured<lb/> your arguments &#38; reasoning by<lb/> word of mouth will have a<lb/> happier tendency than letter<lb/> communications&#8212;<persName>Mrs Moses</persName><lb/> desires her kind regards to you<lb/> In hopes of <hi rend="underline">soon</hi> hearing from<lb/> you I am Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Very Resptly Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Perry Moses</persName></p>
				<p>N. B. Please regard </p>
				<p>this letter as private.</p>
		</body>
